\begin_layout Subsection
Temperature coupling
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since the temperature is dependent on the velocities of the particles within
 the system one method (that was also used in this thesis) to keep the temperatu
re constant is to scale the velocities as described in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:temp"

\end_inset

.
 A temperature change can be actioned via the scaling of the velocities
 between two time-steps thus the scaling factor can be calculated as follows
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Bussi2007"

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\Delta T & = & \frac{1}{2}\sum\frac{2}{3}\frac{m_{i}(\lambda v_{i})^{2}}{Nk_{B}}-\frac{1}{2}\sum\frac{2}{3}\frac{m_{i}v_{i}^{2}}{Nk_{B}}\label{eq:temp}\\
\Delta T & = & (\lambda^{2}-1)T\,(t)\nonumber \\
\lambda & = & \sqrt{\nicefrac{T_{new}}{T\,(t)}}\nonumber 
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

If the scaling factor 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 is adjusted so that 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{new}$
\end_inset

 is equal to the required temperature (
\begin_inset Formula $T_{req}$
\end_inset

) the temperature of the system can be easily controlled by a single factor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Pressure coupling
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The method used to keep the pressure constant during the production runs
 in this thesis was the Parinello-Rahman barostat 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Parrinello1981"

\end_inset

, which modifies the dimensions of the box in order to adjust the pressure.
 The coupling modifies the velocities as seen in the temperature coupling
 and is shown in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:pre"

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{d^{2}r_{i}}{dt^{2}} & = & \frac{F_{i}}{m_{i}}-M\frac{dr_{i}}{dt}\label{eq:pre}\\
M & = & b^{-1}\left[b\frac{db^{'}}{dt}+\frac{db}{dt}b^{'}\right]b^{'-1}\nonumber 
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 being the matrix of the systems box vectors.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The box vectors are dependent on the difference between the current pressure
 and the reference pressure following equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:preb"

\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{db^{2}}{dt^{2}} & = & V\, W^{-1}b^{'-1}\left(P-P_{ref}\right)\label{eq:preb}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

 Therefore, a change within the pressure of the system changes the dimensions
 of the system which is used to scale the velocities.
\end_layout

